      "message": "This is counter to the polyfill approach we\u0027re using for Metal/SPIRV, but I think it\u0027s justified:\n\nFor Metal and Vulkan, many/most intrinsics are natively supported, so the ones we\u0027re poly-filling with SkSL are just the \"extras\". It\u0027s also *much* easier to write them in SkSL than in the corresponding generators (string pasting or spirv-op sequences).\n\nFor SkVM, *all* intrinsics need to be implemented, so the previous divide was arbitrary (which ones were difficult or cumbersome to implement in the byte code generator).",
